The street lights in Van Wijk Street burnt during the day on Wednesday.  According to residents these lights have been on 24 hours of the day for months and nothing is being done. LEES OOK: Vaccinate your pets to prevent rabies outbreak  These street lights are the responsibility of the City of Mbombela Local Municipality (CMLC).  CMLC spokesman did not respond to any of the enquiries made by Lowvelder. LEES OOK: Community finding solutions for noise pollution  